text: Terézia Kulová (born 2 April 1997) is a Slovak footballer who plays as a defender for Slovan Bratislava in the Slovak Women's First League and has appeared for the Slovakia women's national team. ==Career== Kulová has been capped for the Slovakia national team, appearing for the team during the 2019 FIFA Women's World Cup qualifying cycle. ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Slovak women's footballers Category:Slovakia women's international footballers Category:Women's association football defenders Category:ŠK Slovan Bratislava (women) players
